{"sections":{"ec32b834-e4e2-4e87-8392-6d45f7b82d33":{"type":"text-with-media","blocks":{"template--16177341137065__ec32b834-e4e2-4e87-8392-6d45f7b82d33-image-1":{"type":"image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/JOANNA_NATALIE_MARIE_07.jpg"}}},"block_order":["template--16177341137065__ec32b834-e4e2-4e87-8392-6d45f7b82d33-image-1"],"settings":{"remove_spacing_top":false,"remove_spacing_bottom":true,"enable_newsletter_subscribe":false,"klaviyo_form_id":"","media_position":"left","media_width":"7","content_position":"middleLeft","subheading":"","title":"<p>Rumi | Lensed By Joanna Halpin<\/p>","description":"<p>Rumi, our latest collection brought to life by NMJ muse <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/joannahalpin\/?hl=en\"><strong>Joanna Halpin<\/strong><\/a><strong>, <\/strong>whose creative eye shapes these forms, forged from raw materials, giving us a glimpse into a moment in time.<\/p>","colour_style":"dark","button_1_text":"","button_1_link":"","button_style":"underline"}},"3ebc68a8-39a5-4ef0-96ec-3daf87a7a4fc":{"type":"seo-copy","disabled":true,"settings":{"title":"","content_intro":"<p><strong>DO: BUY WHAT YOU LOVE<\/strong><\/p><p><em>Natalie: <\/em>Simply, a piece of vintage jewellery should be chosen because it resonates with you, and because you fall in love with it. Not only are they imbued with the histories and stories of their past owners, but vintage jewellery also provides an opportunity to embrace sustainable purchasing habits – offering once-cherished designs a second (or third) lease on life.<\/p><p>I have always had a love for vintage jewellery, or vintage anything really. I used to spend hours in op shops collecting all sorts of odd finds – furniture, clothes, hats, even once a vintage suitcase which I used to transport and display my first ever collection! I love the mystery and enigmatic nature of vintage pieces, the opportunity for speculation on their history and journey. I also have a deep reverence for the incredible craftsmanship many of these piece’s hold. So much tradition and heritage exists in every tiny detail, which is where my love for vintage jewellery originates from.<\/p><p>I encourage you to find your spark. Is it a particular stone colour or cut, the setting or design style or maybe even the piece’s provenance and era that speaks to you? Is it because it reminds you of a place, someone special or loved ones from generations past? I always like to remind clients that jewellery doesn’t have to be engraved or marked with a special stone to become solely yours – it can be anything about the piece that sparks a feeling or takes you back to a moment in time.<\/p><p>There’s a sense of romance and allure inherit in vintage pieces, and finding the perfect design should feel akin to falling in love: a lightning bolt of recognition; the sense that you two were destined to be connected.<\/p>","content":""}},"22942553-01da-4697-89ac-f500b502883f":{"type":"content-list","blocks":{"template--16177341137065__22942553-01da-4697-89ac-f500b502883f-image-3":{"type":"image","settings":{"apply_overlay":false,"devices":"mobile_desktop","content_position":"underLeft","subheading":"","title":"","description":"<p>Born from the scenic coast of South West England, Joanna first embarked on her career as a model in London during her early twenties. From here she has moved behind the camera and unearthed a distinctive visual tone.<br\/><br\/>She captures the beauty shaped by her surroundings in a uniquely evocative light. Her eye for detail and affinity for subtle storytelling has made her one of the most sought-after visual artists, with brands around the world seeking her thoughtful, aesthetic sensibility.<br\/><br\/>Known for her ability to embrace the soft and moody, Joanna honours beauty in quiet, often overlooked moments. Her approach reveals an innate talent for uncovering hidden nuances, and translating visual language. <br\/><br\/>In addition to her roots in the UK, Joanna considers Sydney, Australia, one of her surrogate homes— a place she often retreats to for inspiration and renewal. Now based in New York, she continues to expand her artistic pursuits, balancing projects across the globe while capturing the beauty she sees through her lens.<\/p>","description_mobile":"<p>Born from the scenic coast of South West England, Joanna first embarked on her career as a model in London during her early twenties. From here she has moved behind the camera and unearthed a distinctive visual tone.<br\/><br\/>She captures the beauty shaped by her surroundings in a uniquely evocative light. Her eye for detail and affinity for subtle storytelling has made her one of the most sought-after visual artists, with brands around the world seeking her thoughtful, aesthetic sensibility.<br\/><br\/>Known for her ability to embrace the soft and moody, Joanna honours beauty in quiet, often overlooked moments. Her approach reveals an innate talent for uncovering hidden nuances, and translating visual language. <br\/><br\/>In addition to her roots in the UK, Joanna considers Sydney, Australia, one of her surrogate homes— a place she often retreats to for inspiration and renewal. Now based in New York, she continues to expand her artistic pursuits, balancing projects across the globe while capturing the beauty she sees through her lens.<\/p>","colour_style":"dark","button_1_metaobject":"","button_1_text":"","button_1_link":"","button_2_metaobject":"","button_2_text":"","button_2_link":"","button_3_metaobject":"","button_3_text":"","button_3_link":"","button_style":"underline","include_no_media_border":false,"metaobject_autoplay":"","metaobject_loop":"","metaobject_apply_overlay":"","metaobject_content_position":"","metaobject_colour_style":"","metaobject_button_style":"","metaobject_devices":""}}},"block_order":["template--16177341137065__22942553-01da-4697-89ac-f500b502883f-image-3"],"settings":{"grid_items_count":3,"grid_items_count_pocket":"1\/2","text_align":"center","subheading":""